{{Quote|So that's what it means to be a witch? Killing people to serve your own agenda? No. Not for me.|Billy Maximoff to [[Agatha Harkness]]|Darkest Hour / Wake Thy Power}}
'''William "Billy" Maximoff''' is the son of [[Wanda Maximoff]] and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] and the younger twin brother of [[Tommy Maximoff]]. Created by Wanda through her [[Magic#Chaos Magic|chaos magic]], Billy was born and raised within the [[Westview Anomaly]], where he and his brother were rapidly aged up, and Billy was bestowed with the ability to read minds as well as his mother's chaos magic. Maximoff and his brother were briefly [[Kidnapping of Billy and Tommy Maximoff|kidnapped]] by the witch [[Agatha Harkness]], but were freed by their mother, and the twins participated in the [[Battle of Westview]], defeating [[S.W.O.R.D.]] agents. Following the battle, Wanda chose to dispel the Westview Anomaly, which resulted in the twins' bodies dematerializing. In an attempt to save himself and Tommy, Billy used his [[magic]] to remove their souls before they could be deleted. Maximoff then transferred his soul into the recently deceased body of [[William Kaplan]]. Maximoff, who became amnesiac, then lived for three years as '''William Kaplan'''.

In [[2026]], having studied witchcraft, he realized his true identity and sought to find Tommy. Reuniting with Harkness, Maximoff unknowingly used his chaos magic to create the fabled [[Witches' Road]] and endured trials as a member of Harkness' [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|new coven]]. With Harkness' help, Maximoff regained some of his memories, located Tommy's soul, and transferred it into [[Thomas Shepherd]]'s dead body. The completion of the Road allowed Maximoff to harness the full extent of his power and he embraced the moniker of '''Wiccan'''. He then arrived to save Harkness from [[Death]], although the [[Skirmish at Agnes O'Connor's House|battle]] ended with Harkness' death. She then returned as a [[Ghosts|ghost]] to serve as Maximoff's spirit guide, and the pair set off to find Tommy.

==Biography==
{{MD|William Maximoff (Earth-199999)}}
===Pre-Existence===
====Prophesied====
[[File:Wiccan Statue.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff's statue in the [[Darkhold Castle]]]]
In ancient times, [[Chthon]], a [[Demons|demonic]] entity, built the [[Darkhold Castle]] atop [[Mount Wundagore]]. There, Chthon prophesied the existence of a powerful entity known as [[Scarlet Witch]], as well as her son Billy Maximoff, who would inherit her [[magic]]al abilities. A statue of Maximoff was built in the castle.{{Ref|DSitMoM}}

===[[Westview Anomaly]]===
====Created by Wanda Maximoff====
[[File:Wanda's Baby.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff in his baby crib]]
{{Quote|There's another baby coming!"<br>"Billy?!|[[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] and [[Wanda Maximoff]]|Now in Color}}
William "Billy" Maximoff was created by [[Wanda Maximoff]] using her [[Magic|Chaos Magic]]. Following an unnaturally fast pregnancy, he was born shortly after his twin brother [[Tommy Maximoff]] to their parents, Wanda and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]], in the [[Vision Residence]] in [[Westview]]. Upon being checked over by Doctor [[Stan Nielson]], the newborn twins were put to bed as Wanda and [[Geraldine]] watched over them. Having reminisced about her own twin brother [[Pietro Maximoff]], Wanda sung the babies a [[Sokovian Lullaby]] to get them to settle. When Geraldine recognized the name Pietro, she inquired about Wanda's history with [[Ultron]]. Becoming more and more aggravated, Wanda interrogated Geraldine about how she knew Pietro. In response to the adults' confrontation, Billy and Tommy started to cry until Wanda used her powers to eject Geraldine from Westview. Billy and Tommy calmed down again once Wanda returned to them in their crib.{{Ref|WV103}}{{Ref|WV104}}

====Growing Up Fast====
[[File:Wanda, Billy & Tommy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff with his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]] and [[Tommy Maximoff|twin brother]]]]
{{Quote|Kids. Can't control 'em. No matter how hard you try.|"[[Agatha Harkness|Agnes O'Connor]]"|On a Very Special Episode...}}
Shortly after Billy and Tommy were born, [[Wanda Maximoff]] and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] grew increasingly frustrated as the twins refused to sleep and instead were crying. As Wanda and Vision were attempting to get their newborn children to sleep, "[[Agatha Harkness|Agnes O'Connor]]" walked into the [[Vision Residence]]. She offered to take care of the babies for them to relieve some of their stress. Eventually, the exhausted parents noticed that the children were quiet, but soon realized they were not in their cribs. They soon realized that the twins' ages had accelerated and that they had grown from newborns to five-year-olds.
[[File:Tommy & Billy (Age 10).png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy and [[Tommy Maximoff]] age themselves up]]
Later, Billy and his brother found a stray [[dog]] in their street, and brought him to their kitchen, intending to bathe him so their mother would let them keep him. When Wanda discovered the dog, she warned them that taking care of a dog was a huge responsibility. Vision later walked in as well, and so did "O'Connor", carrying a doghouse for the new family pet, whom they named [[Sparky]]. However, when Vision insisted that the twins were not old enough for a dog, Billy and Tommy looked at each other mischievously. They then aged themselves once more, this time to ten-year-olds.
[[File:Wanda & the Twins WV Ep5.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Billy listens to [[Wanda Maximoff]]]]
Later that day, Billy trained Sparky to do tricks and fed him treats. When Tommy insisted that they go to show their father, Wanda informed them that he was at work. The twins found this confusing as it was a Saturday, so he was not supposed to be working. Wanda told them he needed a distraction. However, Billy believed that he needed a distraction from them. Wanda quickly explained that that was not the case, and said to them that while he and Tommy would argue at time, they would always be brothers. Tommy asked if Wanda had a brother, and Wanda said that she did, but that he was far away from here. The twins and their mother would then be distracted by Sparky running to the door, something attracting his attention. As Wanda went outside to investigate, she opened the door only for Sparky to run away, which caught Billy and Tommy's attention. Billy and Tommy then went outside to find Sparky while accompanying their mother.
[[File:Agnes Holding Dead Sparky.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff discovers that [[Sparky]] has died]]
Shortly after, Wanda, Billy and Tommy were walking around their street looking for Sparky, who had run away earlier. They soon were approached by "O'Connor", who was holding Sparky in a blanket, and she informed Billy and Tommy that he had died. The twins were shocked and devastated, and attempted to again age themselves. However, Wanda stopped them before they could do anything. They begged for Wanda to resurrect Sparky, however, Wanda insisted she could not do such a thing. Vision arrived soon after and saw that Sparky had died, and comforted his sons.{{Ref|WV105}}

====First Halloween====
[[File:Billy Maximoff (Documentary).png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy talks about Halloween]]
{{Quote|I hear [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Dad]] in my head. He's in trouble.|Billy Maximoff to [[Wanda Maximoff]]|All-New Halloween Spooktacular!}}
The next day, Billy got dressed into his Halloween costume and talked about Halloween while getting video-taped. He then joined Tommy in pranking their uncle [[Ralph Bohner|Pietro Maximoff]], who was lying on the couch. Shortly, [[Wanda Maximoff]] walked down the stairs, in her costume, and then greeted [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] who joined them in his costume. Billy then watched as "Pietro" whisked Tommy away and then returned wearing matching costumes and hairstyles.
[[File:Billy hears Vision.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy hears [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] in his head]]
Billy then enjoyed the Halloween festivities with Tommy and "Pietro." Later that evening, Billy and Tommy approached Wanda and showed her their newfound powers. Billy was able to telepathically move objects, like his mother. Billy and Tommy then left to get candy at the end of the street, before returning to the main square. Billy then used his powers to halt an excited Tommy, as he used his mind to see Vision in distress outside next to [[S.W.O.R.D.]] agents, and immediately rushed to inform Wanda. Billy then watched in shock when Wanda used her powers to blast "Pietro" into a haystack.{{Ref|WV106}}

====[[Kidnapping of Billy and Tommy Maximoff|Abducted by Agatha Harkness]]====
[[File:Billy & Tommy Maximoff.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Billy asks his [[Scarlet Witch|mother]] for help]]
{{Quote|Mom, help!|Billy Maximoff to [[Wanda Maximoff]]|Previously On}}
The next morning, Billy and [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]] played video games in the living room, while waiting for their [[Scarlet Witch|mother]] to wake up. However, their games began switching throughout different time periods. Confused, Billy and Tommy went up to Wanda's bedroom and asked her what was happening. However, Wanda didn't want to be bothered and told them she wanted to sleep. Billy then told her that he could hear voices in his head, meaning that he could hear the other [[Westview]] citizens.
[[File:Billy Maximoff Reaction.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy witnesses his [[Scarlet Witch|mother]]'s breakdown]]
Billy and Tommy then returned downstairs and waited for Wanda. When she came down, she told them to stay away from "Pietro" and that Vision would return when he was ready. She then began to have a mental breakdown, confusing Billy and Tommy.
[[File:Agnes takes Billy & Tommy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy and [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]] go with [[Agatha Harkness|Agnes]]]]
After Wanda sat down with them, [[Agatha Harkness|Agnes]] arrived and walked inside. Seeing that Wanda was stressed out, she then offered to watch Billy and Tommy at her house while Wanda got feeling better. Wanda agreed and Billy and Tommy left with Agnes.
[[File:Billy, Agatha & Tommy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy with [[Agatha Harkness|Agnes]], [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]], and [[Señor Scratchy]]]]
After being taken to Agnes' [[Agnes O'Connor's House|house]], Billy and Tommy sat down on the couch in the living room and Billy played with [[Señor Scratchy]], who laid in his lap. When Agnes joined them on the couch, Billy told her that she was silent and that he couldn't hear her thoughts. Agnes then reassured them that their mother would be fine. Agnes then made Billy and Tommy sandwiches and turned on the television for them, before locking them up in her witch lair.{{Ref|WV107}}
[[File:Billy choked by Agatha.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy choked by [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
Billy and Tommy were then brought out to the street by [[Agatha Harkness]] and restrained by her magic, causing them to choke. They then cried out when they saw Wanda run out and try to rescue them.{{Ref|WV108}} After Harkness declared Wanda the "Scarlet Witch", Wanda blasted Harkness away, allowing Billy and Tommy to run into their house.{{Ref|WV109}}

====[[Battle of Westview]]====
[[File:Tommy & Billy dying.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy disappearing]]
{{Quote|Boys, handle the [[S.W.O.R.D.|military]]. Mommy will be right back.|[[Wanda Maximoff]] to Billy Maximoff and [[Tommy Maximoff]]|The Series Finale}}
Inside the house, Billy saw a vision of Wanda in the Westview town square and told Tommy that she needed help. After running to the town square, however, Billy and Tommy fell to the ground and began to disappear as Wanda was getting rid of the [[Hex]]. When Wanda saw this, she stopped and embraced Billy, Tommy, and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]].
[[File:Billy Maximoff.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy uses his powers to defeat the [[S.W.O.R.D.]] agents]]
Wanda then put a force field around them as [[Agatha Harkness]] tried to shoot them with her powers. After Harkness had absorbed Wanda's powers, [[S.W.O.R.D.]] agents in Humvees arrived, followed by [[White Vision]]. Wanda told Billy and Tommy to handle the agents while she dealt with Harkness. Billy then used his powers to mind control the agents, while Tommy sped around and took some of the agents' belongings. Billy then watched as [[Tyler Hayward]] stepped out of his Humvee and aimed at them with his gun. However, they were saved by [[Monica Rambeau]].
[[File:Billy, Monica & Tommy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy meets [[Monica Rambeau]]]]
Rambeau used her new powers to absorb the bullets, but when she missed one, Billy stopped the bullet and threw it to the ground. Hayward, enraged, hopped into another Humvee and prepared to ram them, but was ultimately prevented from doing so. Billy then told Rambeau that he liked her powers. They then ran over to meet with Vision, and then watched as Wanda fought Harkness in the sky. Billy then reunited with Wanda, having embraced her role as the Scarlet Witch, and watched as she transformed Harkness back into "Agnes".{{Ref|WV109}}

====Dissolution of the Hex====
[[File:Wanda & Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Billy says good night to his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]]]]
{{Quote|It's nice. That feeling when your body knows it's safe."<br>"Breathe with [[Tommy Maximoff|him]]. Breathe."<br>"The sound of him. It stops because everything else does."<br>"It's your [[Scarlet Witch|mother]] folding her [[Westview Anomaly|world]].|Billy Maximoff and [[Agatha Harkness]]|Follow Me My Friend / To Glory at the End}}
Billy then left the town square with his family and returned [[Vision Residence|home]]. There, [[Wanda Maximoff|Wanda]] and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] tucked Billy and [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]] into their beds and bid them good night. Billy then smiled at his mother as she thanked him and Tommy for making her a mother. As she left their bedroom, the [[Hex]], which was being dispelled, began to work its way towards their family home.{{Ref|WV109}} Billy was about to go to sleep, and noted how quickly his brother had fallen asleep and focused on Tommy's breathing. However, Billy then noticed he could no longer hear his surroundings, including Tommy's breathing, due to the Hex dissolving. Using his mind-reading ability, Billy overheard his parents' last words with each other. In a desperate bid to save himself and his brother, Billy's [[magic]] removed their souls from their bodies.{{Ref|AAA108}}

===Taking Over William Kaplan===
====Transferring His Soul====
[[File:Billy Maximoff Kaplan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff's soul is transferred to [[William Kaplan]]'s dead body]]
{{Quote|You survived like witches have been doing for centuries. You saw an opportunity, an [[William Kaplan|empty vessel]], and you moved in. So you broke the rules. Big deal. That's what kept you alive.|[[Agatha Harkness]] to Billy Maximoff|Familiar by Thy Side}}
As [[Scarlet Witch]] was terminating the [[Westview Anomaly]], the Kaplan family was driving home. [[Rebecca Kaplan]] became distracted by the Hex and drove into a ditch, and her thirteen year old son [[William Kaplan|William]] took the full force as they smashed into a tree, subsequently cracking his head on the window. As William's heart stopped beating,{{Ref|AAA106}} Maximoff, whose corporeal form was disappearing due to the Westview Anomaly being dispelled, transferred his soul into the newly deceased body,<ref>[https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/agatha-all-along-joe-locke-billy-maximoff-reveal 'Agatha All Along' Star Joe Locke Breaks Down That Big Billy Maximoff Episode]</ref> which had an existing [[Glossary#Sigil|sigil]] on it, making it so no witch could know his name. He then woke up yelling for [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]]. However, he had been rendered with amnesia. With the help of Officer [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]], he was taken to the hospital.{{Ref|AAA106}}

====Amnesia====
[[File:Bloody Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|"William" transported in an ambulance]]
{{Quote|It's fine. Just please don't fight."<br>"What do you mean?"<br>"We're not fighting.|"William Kaplan", [[Rebecca Kaplan]], and [[Jeff Kaplan]]|Familiar by Thy Side}}
He then looked at the glass and saw what he looked like, and did not seem to recognize his own appearance. Days later in the [[Eastview General Hospital]], he was shocked to realize he had the ability to read minds and listened to [[Rebecca Kaplan|Rebecca]] and [[Jeff Kaplan]] talking with the doctor about his amnesia. 
[[File:Billiam in the Hospital.png|{{AltFloat}}|"William" listens to his parents' thoughts]]
Using it again once his parents walked in, he heard what the Kaplans were thinking. He then asked them not to fight, which they said they were not. Rebecca then talked about what the doctor said, stating that the amnesia would just need time to resolve itself on its own, and that he was to be discharged by the next day.{{Ref|AAA106}}

====Accepting a New Identity====
[[File:Billiam Comes Home.png|{{AltFloat}}|"William" enters the [[Kaplan Residence]]]]
{{Quote|My name is William Kaplan. I'm William Kaplan. I am William Kaplan.|William Kaplan|Familiar by Thy Side}}
The next day, the family arrived [[Kaplan Residence|home]]. Entering the unfamiliar domicile, he looked around and saw the family photos. He then saw himself in the mirror again. Suddenly, [[Greg (Dog)|Greg]] came in barking at him which [[Rebecca Kaplan|Rebecca]] chalked up as the smell from the hospital.
[[File:Split Life Line.png|{{AltFloat}}|"William" embraces the [[William Kaplan]] identity]]
He then used his mind-reading powers and listened to the Kaplans being worried. He listened some more as he heard his parents just wanting his old self back. As these voices became overwhelming, he lashed out, yelling at them to stop worrying. Realizing what he had done, he apologized and asked to see his room. He then said they could have dinner when he came back down. He then entered "his" room and looked around. He saw the many posters on the walls and ceiling indicating a love for magic. He then walked towards the mirror and saw his reflection. Deciding to embrace the identity of his new life, he told himself that his name was [[William Kaplan]].{{Ref|AAA106}}

====Fascination with Magic====
{{Quote|I bid on a limited edition signed LP of the [[Ballad of the Witches' Road|Ballad]], but it cost more than I make in a whole summer at the [[Hokey Pokey Bowl]].|Billy Maximoff|Circle Sewn With Fate / Unlock Thy Hidden Gate}}
Kaplan continued has fascination with magic and became a fan of [[Lorna Wu and the Coral Shore]]. He tried to get a signed LP of the [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]], but it cost more than what he earned at his job, the [[Hokey Pokey Bowl]].{{Ref|AAA102}}

===Discovering His Past===
====Confession to Eddie====
[[File:William and Eddie Kiss.png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan and [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] kiss]]
{{Quote|I do have one question."<br>"Just one?"<br>"If you're not [[William Kaplan]], who are you?|[[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] and William Kaplan|Familiar by Thy Side}}
By [[2026]], Kaplan met [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]], who soon became his boyfriend. However, he still wondered about his past before the crash as he still suffered from amnesia. Therefore, he held onto the sigil that he found in his pocket before the crash. One night, Kaplan was on a date with Eddie when Eddie brought up the sigil. The two then started kissing until Kaplan used his powers and heard that Eddie wanted to confess his love.
[[File:William Confession.png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan confesses that he is not William]]
Kaplan then backed away and apologized, saying he needed to tell Eddie something, although Eddie said that he had something to say too. Kaplan then started talking about the crash and stated that he died that night and when he came back he was different. He confessed he was not entirely [[William Kaplan]]. He informed Eddie that he did not remember anything from prior to the accident and only pretended to so his parents would not worry. He added that nothing in his life was normal until he met Eddie and he loved Eddie as well. Upon sharing a tender moment and exchange of romantic affirmations, Eddie then asked who he was if he was not William Kaplan.{{Ref|AAA106}}

====Research====
[[File:Billiam and Eddie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan and [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] laugh about [[Kale Kare]]]]
{{Quote|Those are runes. This was a spell. Witchcraft. People who were there refuse to talk about it. But I did find this [[Ralph Bohner|guy]] on {{WPS|Reddit}}. He used to live [[Westview|there]]. I'm supposed to meet him tomorrow.|William Kaplan to [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]]|Familiar by Thy Side}}
Kaplan brought [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] to his room to show his research on his past. However, Kaplan noted that Eddie needed to put his jacket back on because his physique was distracting. Kaplan talked about the [[Westview Anomaly]], which Eddie believed to be an [[Avengers]] practice gone wrong. Kaplan called him adorably trusting. He then opened his computer, only to play a video from [[Jennifer Kale]]. Kaplan exited that video and brought up a video of the Hex.
[[File:Billiam Research.png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan tells [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] about runes]]
During the video, Kaplan paused on a frame to reveal there were runes in the sky, meaning a witch had cast it. Kaplan then noted that he was going to meet with someone the next day who had information about the Hex. Upon hearing he found this man on {{WPS|Reddit}}, Eddie turned the previous mockery around, calling Kaplan adorably trusting.{{Ref|AAA106}}

====Speaking with Ralph Bohner====
[[File:Agatha All Along Autoplay Menu (Familiar by Thy Side).jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan meets [[Ralph Bohner]]]]
{{Quote|Please don't ask about [[Agatha Harkness]]. Please don't ask about Agatha Harkness."<br>"What do you know about Agatha Harkness?|[[Ralph Bohner]] and William Kaplan|Familiar by Thy Side}}
The next day in a parking garage, Kaplan and [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] waited for the man to emerge. They then saw him as he blocked out secruity cameras. Although Eddie got worried, Kaplan jumped out to met him. Upon confirmation of their identities, the man turned around to face Kaplan, saying to call him [[Ralph Bohner]]. Bohner then corrected himself, stating his alias, Randall, before realizing he messed it up. Bohner then checked for wires as he was untrusting.
[[File:William Talks with Bohner.png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan learns about the [[Westview Anomaly]]]]
Bohner then yelled at them to get down when a noise startled him. Kaplan asked Bohner to start with what he remembered. Bohner revealed he remembered everything and that [[Wanda Maximoff]] had the entire town acting out a sitcom. Kaplan asked if it changed Bohner, could he do "stuff", referring to powers. Bohner stated that he woke up every night screaming. Kaplan then listened to Bohner's thoughts as he did not want Kaplan to ask about [[Agatha Harkness]].
[[File:William Learns About Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan learns about Billy and [[Tommy Maximoff]]]]
Naturally, Kaplan did ask about her, angering Bohner. Bohner then took out witch repellent and sprayed the two teens before remarking a ritual to protect himself. Bohner then went to leave until he turned around and decided to talk more for extra money. Among other things, Bohner stated he was a terrible influence on Maximoff's twin sons, Billy and [[Tommy Maximoff]]. Upon hearing the name Tommy, Kaplan remembered the name. Bohner then revealed Tommy was a speedster and Billy could read minds. Kaplan then asked what happened to them and Bohner revealed they simply disappeared. Finally, Bohner revealed that Harkness still lived in [[Westview]] under a spell.{{Ref|AAA106}}

====Witch Research====
[[File:Agatha All Along Teaser Trailer (89).png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan listens to the [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]]]]
{{Quote|Release spell. Requires an important personal item.|William Kaplan|Familiar by Thy Side}}
Kaplan returned [[Kaplan Residence|home]] to hear his [[Jeff Kaplan|father]] ask where [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] was. Kaplan said he went home. Kaplan then went up to his room to finish research on his past. During the research, Kaplan listed to [[Lorna Wu and the Coral Shore]]'s rendition of the [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]] and got the idea of researching [[Agatha Harkness]]. Upon doing so, he decided to go to [[Westview]] and release her from her spell. In order to do so, he needed a personal item of hers.{{Ref|AAA106}}

===A New Quest===
====[[Liberation of Agatha Harkness|Saving Agatha Harkness]]====
{{Quote|See, I feel like you've typecast me as the mouthy teen who didn't actually kill the victim but is guilty of some other B-story crime. Well, that couldn't be farther from the truth.|William Kaplan to "[[Agnes O'Connor]]"|Familiar by Thy Side}}
Kaplan arrived in [[Westview]] and looked at a text from [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]], who signed it with a black heart.{{Ref|AAA106}} Kaplan then broke into [[Agnes O'Connor's House|Agatha Harkness' House]] and found her [[Agatha Harkness' Locket|locket]], which he was going to use as the personal item. However, he toppled over a lamp, causing it to crash. Harkness then chased Kaplan down the street until he was hit by [[Sharon Davis]], who was merely opening her door.
[[File:Agatha Over Billy.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan is interrogated by [[Agnes O'Connor]]]]
Now captured, Harkness interrogated Kaplan, believing herself to be a detective while under her spell. Kaplan tried to explain the situation, but everything he said was becoming filtered through the spell, leading Harkness to dramatically call him a loser. She then placed down photos of what she believed to be a corpse on the table. Kaplan simply said they were just daisies. Suddenly, the spell started breaking apart. Seeing an opportunity, Kaplan started reciting his spell until Harkness got him to stop by tying him up. She then threw Kaplan into the closet. Later on, a freed Harkness opened the door to find Kaplan still there.{{Ref|AAA106}}{{Ref|AAA101}}

====Teaming Up====
[[File:Agatha All Along Revealed (22).png|{{AltFloat}}|Kaplan tries to convince [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
{{Quote|My name is [[William Kaplan]]."<br>"Say again."<br>"I'm Billy Maximoff.|Billy Maximoff and [[Agatha Harkness]]|Familiar by Thy Side}}
Kaplan inched out of the closet to find [[Agatha Harkness]] frantically trying to find items. Kaplan then started speaking through his duct tape, making Harkness rip it off. Kaplan then asked for her to take him down the [[Witches' Road]]. Harkness refused because of the consequences and pure disinterest. Trying to appeal, Kaplan talked about how much he knew of Harkness and talked about freeing her. She got interested hearing that he broke a spell cast by [[Scarlet Witch]].
[[File:I'm Billy Maximoff.png|{{AltFloat}}|He embraces the Billy Maximoff identity]]
Harkness still wanted to leave. However, she stopped when Kaplan brought up the [[Salem Seven]] and how they were coming for her. Harkness picked up her [[Agatha Harkness' Locket|locket]] and turned around, asking Kaplan who he was.{{Ref|AAA102}} Kaplan stated he was "William Kaplan",{{Ref|AAA106}} but a sigil appeared on his mouth that he could not perceive, preventing her from hearing him.{{Ref|AAA102}} She asked again, and he changed his answer to "Billy Maximoff",{{Ref|AAA106}} although she still could not hear it. Harkness became intrigued and he asked why. Harkness did not clarify and walked away.{{Ref|AAA102}}

====[[Search for Coven Members|Finding a Coven]]====
[[File:Teen and Agatha.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff follows [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
{{Quote|So, with a Covenstead, it's unlikely we'll find witches as high-profile as you."<br>"Yeah, there's no such thing, Teen.|Billy Maximoff and [[Agatha Harkness]]|Circle Sewn With Fate / Unlock Thy Hidden Gate}}
[[Agatha Harkness]] gave Maximoff a pair of scissors to cut himself out and said he was driving. Maximoff chased after Harkness as she asked what he knew about covens. Maximoff replied with his knowledge before stopping to excitedly ask if she was bringing him to her [[Salemites|coven]]. Harkness told him they were all dead. However, they do need a coven to access the road. They then stopped in front of an empty [[Vision Residence|lot]]. As Harkness looked at it, Maximoff told her his car was to the side.
[[File:Billy driving Agatha.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff drives with [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
On the way out of [[Westview]], Maximoff was called by [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]]. However, Maximoff declined, remarking that he gets worried. He then asked how they will find the coven, to where Harkness quoted that wherever they go, a coven there shall be. She then clarified, saying that within a three mile radius, they should find witches. Maximoff asked her to write that down in his book, but she ignored him by throwing the pen out of the window.
