===The Witches' Road===
====[[Potions Witch Trial]]====
[[File:Analog Magic.png|{{AltFloat}}|The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] on the [[Witches' Road]]]]
{{Quote|Hey, a bit of advice. Watch your back with [[Agatha Harkness|Agatha]]."<br>"I know how people feel about her."<br>"Did you know she traded her own [[Nicholas Scratch|child]] for the [[Darkhold|Book of the Damned]]?|[[Jennifer Kale]] and Billy Maximoff|Through Many Miles / Of Tricks and Trials}}
Maximoff walked down the [[Witches' Road]] with [[Agatha Harkness]] and remarked at how it was how he pictured it. Harkness noted that it suited him. [[Jennifer Kale]] asked [[Salem Seven]] was following them and blamed Harkness. Maximoff spoke up saying that since they were a [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]], they shared burdens. Kale then asked if they should call Maximoff's parents. Maximoff stated he was sure they were asleep at the time unless the road resembled night as a "vibe".
[[File:Billy's Sigil E3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff's sigil reveals itself]]
As they walked further, they realized that the road would show their greatest fears through trials. Harkness told them that they had to pass the trial with each skill. An annoyed Kale asked how they would do that without power. Maximoff brought up how they could do analog magic. Kale then asked who he was again, still confused. Maximoff stated his name, only to see everyone get taken aback. [[Lilia Calderu]] remarked that someone had put a sigil on him.
[[File:Agatha All Along - Agatha's Coven.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|[[Agatha Harkness' Coven]] sees the [[Witches' Road Beach House]]]]
As they talked, they realized that [[Sharon Davis]] had disappeared. Suddenly, cries rang out from a distance. The group ran over and saw Davis being swallowed up by mud. They helped her get out. They then were stopped by a bright light. Looking ahead, they realized that a [[Witches' Road Beach House|mansion]] had been conjured in front of them. Upon entering, they noticed their attire had changed, with Maximoff now sporting a sweater and combed hair.
[[File:Billy reads invitation.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff finds the riddle]]
As Maximoff looked around, he stated that it had middle-aged, second chance at love aesthetic. Suddenly, Davis' voice was heard once again; this time, it was her reaction to the beautiful kitchen before her. On the mantle, Maximoff noticed a letter and took it down. Harkness then took it out of Maximoff's hand before Kale did the same to her. Kale realized it was a riddle. Davis then turned around and noticed a wine bottle behind them.
[[File:Billy Kaplan hears Agatha rumors.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff listens to [[Jennifer Kale]]'s warning]]
An oblivious Davis reached over for the bottle, but [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] stopped her because of the danger. Harkness agreed but said they had to drink it or else the trial would not move forward. Harkness asked for a corkscrew and Maximoff walked over to the bar to find one. Kale followed him and decided to give him a talk. She told Maximoff not to trust Harkness and revealed that Harkness had traded her own [[Nicholas Scratch|son]] for the [[Darkhold]]. Maximoff refused to believe her.
[[File:Alice and Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff talks to [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]]]]
Maximoff soon rejoined the group and witnessed them drink the wine, which Maximoff did not do because of his age. Suddenly, a timer started counting down from thirty minutes. The group then sat down as Maximoff tried to make small talk. He asked Wu-Gulliver about her tattoo, but she refused to say where it was from, so Maximoff dropped it. 
[[File:Billy looks at Alice.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff in the [[Witches' Road Beach House]]]]
However, Wu-Gulliver spoke up, saying she got it in [[Colorado]] because her [[Lorna Wu|mother]] claimed all of the women in her family were [[Wu Family Curse|cursed]]. Maximoff asked how old she was. Wu-Gulliver responded saying she was thirteen. Maximoff noted that a lot [[Kaplan Family Car Crash|happened]] to him at thirteen as well. Wu-Gulliver smiled and told him she missed the eyeliner, but his hair was cute. Suddenly, Davis spoke and the group realized her face was swelling. They then realized they were all swelling. Kale figured out the wine was poison.
[[File:Billy commands Agatha to drink.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff demands [[Agatha Harkness]] to drink the [[Alewife's Revenge|poison]]]]
Soon, their faces stopped swelling, making Kale further realize that the poison was [[Alewife's Revenge]]. Maximoff decided to jot this down in his spell book. Scared, Harkness started smashing the window until they got her to stop. Maximoff then realized that Harkness did not drink the poison. Harkness continued to refuse, so Maximoff demanded her to. When she still did not budge, Maximoff decided to drink it himself, only for Harkness to tell him not to. She then drank the poison.
[[File:Alice with Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff smells eucalyptus]]
As Davis passed out from the poison, Kale started creating the antidote as it was her trial. One of the things Kale needed was frankincense, which Wu-Gulliver and Maximoff went to go get. The duo got to a spa area where Wu-Gulliver concluded there was nothing of use. Maximoff stopped her though, saying he smelled eucalyptus. They then ran to the essential oils only for Wu-Gulliver to get lost behind. He returned only to see a frightened Wu-Gulliver crawling on the ground. He helped her up and they rushed back to Kale.
[[File:Lilia, Jennifer, Billy & Alice.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] looks out the window]]
They gave Kale the ingredients only to notice that the glass that Harkness smashed earlier was losing its strength and cracking even more. Furthermore, water had surrounded the mansion. They had to work quickly and carried Davis into the kitchen as Kale used the sink as a cauldron. As they put the ingredients in, Kale told Maximoff to stir counter-clockwise, but had to clarify that meant to the left. Suddenly, Harkness started hallucinating and crying. When she came to, they rushed her to put a strand of her hair in the potion.
[[File:Billy stirs potion.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff stirs the potion]]
Once the potion was mixed, Maximoff and the others held hands as Kale explained that once their intentions were aligned, the potion would glow cerulean. Wu-Gulliver noted that it was green and asked if that was the color. Maximoff told her it was blue. They then realized something went wrong. As Kale thought further, she realized she missed a step: they needed the blood of the unpoisoned. Harkness then took a knife and sliced Maximoff's hand, allowing blood to drip into the potion. It soon turned green.
[[File:AAA Teen.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff pleads for [[Sharon Davis]]' life]]
They drank the antidote and felt relief, only to realize the unconscious Davis did not drink the potion. Maximoff grabbed a glass from Harkness and gave it to Wu-Gulliver, who poured it down Davis' throat as the timer turned to zero. The oven then opened up, revealing the exit. Water then broke through the glass, flooding the place. The group tried to get Davis into the oven, only for Harkness to tell them to leave her. Maximoff refused, saying they could not leave people behind. They then shoved her through and made their exit in the nick of time.{{Ref|AAA103}}

