====[[Protection Witch Trial]]====
[[File:Snazzy Coven.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff and the [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] enter a [[Witches' Road Recording Studio|recording studio]]]]
{{Quote|So, breaking a [[Wu Family Curse|curse]]. Smudge sticks? A salt bath? What if we locate and reason with the witch who cast the curse?|Billy Maximoff|If I Can't Reach You / Let My Song Teach You}}
[[Agatha Harkness' Coven]] arrived at the [[Witches' Road Recording Studio]], which [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] initially refused to enter. However, when she walked the other way, the studio simply conjured itself in front of them again. Upon getting to the door, Harkness remarked how the moon symbol on the door was the waxing phase which was also the fire phase. They entered and noticed how their attire changed again. Maximoff then looked for clues.
[[File:PLAY ME.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff mistakenly plays the demonic song]]
Maximoff found a record player that had a note saying "play me". Maximoff obliged, which started a demonic song that was playing. They realized that the song was playing backwards. [[Agatha Harkness]] soon smashed it to pieces. As everything settled, [[Lilia Calderu]] realized they had been cursed. Suddenly, a metronome started playing. Just as Maximoff stated that nothing seemed to be happening, Calderu fell to the ground in agony as she started burning. Wu-Gulliver used her protection magic to draw a circle around Calderu, saving her.
[[File:Agatha Harkness with Billy Kaplan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff realizes the song is a [[Wu Family Curse|curse]]]]
Maximoff brought up reasoning with the witch who cast the spell, but Harkness told him that a curse cannot be "reeled back in". Calderu said that the only way to end a curse is to face it. Suddenly, [[Jennifer Kale]] started burning up, only for Wu-Gulliver to save her. In panic, they checked the smashed record and figured out it was [[Lorna Wu]]'s rendition of the [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]]. Harkness then realized it was Wu-Gulliver's [[Wu Family Curse|family curse]].
[[File:Agatha All Along Trailer (58).png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff is thrown into a window by the [[Wu Family Curse|curse]]]]
Suddenly, the curse reached Maximoff and threw him backwards into a window. The glass pierced Maximoff's side, but he did not tell this to the rest of the coven and assured everyone he was okay. Soon, the group realized that Wu's ballad was a protection spell for Wu-Gulliver and they had to play it in order to face the curse. Maximoff then started on the guitar as he knew the instrument.
[[File:Billy and his wound.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff painfully looks at his wound]]
They began playing the song and Maximoff helped with his guitar, although he began hunching forward as the glass started giving him immense pain. Eventually, the curse revealed itself, allowing Wu-Gulliver to lure it towards her and kill it. As the commotion stopped, Maximoff cheered weakly, only to collapse from his injury and pass out.
[[File:Injured Teen.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff being healed by the [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]]]]
Maximoff woke up later on the [[Witches' Road]] in a hut. He saw Harkness by his side and immediately asked if she put the sigil on him. Harkness told him she did not, but even if that were the case, the witch that cast it could not remember either. He asked how to lift it, but Harkness told him sigils could not be lifted, only destroyed. It becomes destroyed when it is no longer needed. Maximoff then asked if Harkness killed her [[Nicholas Scratch|son]]. Harkness' face turned cold and she got up and walked away without another sound.{{Ref|AAA104}}

