====[[Spirit Witch Trial]]====
[[File:Darkest Hour, Wake Thy Power Thumbnail.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff during the [[Spirit Witch Trial]]]]
{{Quote|It's too late."<br>"No, it's not! There's a spell, there's always a spell! [[Alice Wu-Gulliver|Alice]], please wake up. Alice! Alice! Come on, Alice. Come on.|[[Lilia Calderu]] and Billy Maximoff|Darkest Hour / Wake Thy Power}}
Upon entering the [[Witches' Road Cabin]], Maximoff's attire changed to a stereotypical teenager sleepover outfit. Maximoff then looked around, realizing he lost his spell book. He soon got over it and looked around the room. He then asked whose trial it was. They realized it was [[Agatha Harkness]]' because of the blood moon which is where the veil is thinnest, so they could talk to the dead.
[[File:Coven at Sleepover.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff and the [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] use the {{WPS|Ouija}} board]]
Maximoff then remarked at how he thought that was [[Lilia Calderu]]'s mastery, but Calderu said it was a common misconception. Suddenly, a board game flew off of the shelf. Maximoff turned it over, revealing it was {{WPS|Ouija}}. Additionally, a timer for thirty minutes went off again. They set it up and Maximoff started reading out the rules, with one being to not taunt the spirits. Maximoff made sure Harkness understood this rule. Upon asking who the spirit was, the board spelled out "[[Mrs. Hart|MRS. HART]]". Suddenly, the board shifted, forcing Calderu's hands off of it, meaning a spirit were to be released.
[[File:Billy Kaplan and Lilia Calderu.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff watches [[Agatha Harkness]]' facade]]
Maximoff watched as Davis became manifested through Harkness, who started talking as if she were Davis. Calderu tried to apologize, but [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] told her it was not Mrs. Hart. Maximoff agreed, saying it was "Sharon Davis". [[Jennifer Kale]] clarified, saying it was neither because Harkness was just playing around. [[Rio Vidal]] then called Harkness scared, making Harkness get serious and sit back down. They then asked who the real spirit was, which stated they were "DEATH". This made Vidal laugh out loud. Maximoff reminded them they were not supposed to ask about death.
[[File:Billy Maximoff (Darkest Hour, Wake Thy Power).png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff tries to save [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
They then asked what "DEATH" wanted. They board soon spelled out "Punish Agatha". The board then spelled out "AGATHA" many times. In fear, Harkness took her hands of the planchet, making the spirit actually come out. The spirit started howling, causing everyone to cover their ears. Wu-Gulliver asked what it wanted. Kale said it wanted to punish Harkness. The howling then stopped. They group realized they needed to punish Harkness to pass the trial. Maximoff argued they should not, but their mind was made up. Suddenly, Harkness disappeared.
[[File:Teen and Possessed Agatha.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff is attacked by [[Evanora Harkness|Agatha Harkness]]]]
The group walked cautiously around the room as Maximoff grabbed a flashlight. He then shined it around the room and up to the ceiling. Upon getting to the ceiling, he saw a possessed Harkness. Harkness then jumped down to the ground and chased a scared Maximoff into the corner. Kale then distracted Harkness away from Maximoff. Harkness then attacked Kale until Calderu turned on the lights, causing Harkness to flee.
[[File:Jennifer, Teen, Lilia, and Alice.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff and the [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] witness [[Evanora Harkness]]]]
They started looking around for Harkness and eventually saw a ghost emerging. The ghost revealed itself as [[Evanora Harkness]]. An unpossessed Agatha then said hello to her mother. Calderu remarked how Evanora and Agatha have unfinished business. Maximoff decided they should finish it. He asked Evanora what she wanted, to which Evanora demanded they finish the [[Witches' Road]] without Agatha. Leaving her with Evanora would be them punishing Agatha.
[[File:Billy Begs to Save Agatha.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff begs to disobey [[Evanora Harkness]]]]
Agatha then talked to her mother, asking why she hated her. Evanora brutally explained that she was evil and she ought to kill her when she was birthed. Kale then told the group they had to go, despite Maximoff telling her not to go. Kale said there was no flood or fire. The threat is Agatha. Agatha then begged the group to take her with them, which Maximoff wanted and tried to do. However, Evanora possessed Agatha again.
[[File:Billy Yells Nicholas Scratch.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff yells out [[Nicholas Scratch]]'s name]]
Wu-Gulliver then attacked Evanora with her powers, sending an energy blast to her. This not only awakened Agatha, but caused her to start draining Wu-Gulliver's power for herself. Maximoff yelled at someone to make her stop, but nobody knew what to do. Suddenly, Maximoff noticed the Ouija board moving, meaning there was another spirit. Maximoff asked who it was and it spelt out "[[Nicholas Scratch|NICHOLAS SCRATCH]]". As the timer dwindled down, Maximoff said the name louder, causing Harkness to stop as Scratch's voice was heard. The door the opened.
[[File:Heartbroken Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff pleads to help [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]]]]
Maximoff set the planchet to "GOOD BYE" and ran over to Wu-Gulliver. To his sorrow, Wu-Gulliver's life was drained, killing her and giving Harkness her powers. Harkness approached the corpse, only for Maximoff to yell at her to get back. Maximoff begged Calderu to do something, but she said it was too late. Maximoff did not agree, saying there was always a spell. He went to check his spell book, only to remember it was gone. He then resorted to begging Wu-Gulliver to wake up, but Kale told him it was too late.{{Ref|AAA105}}

====Sigil Destroyed====
[[File:Agatha All Along Autoplay Menu (Darkest Hour, Wake Thy Power).jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff approaching [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
{{Quote|[[Tommy Maximoff|He]]'s out there somewhere. I can sense him. I just... can't find him."<br>"Gosh, you really are a Maximoff. Otherwise, none of this would be nearly as dramatic."<br>"He's my brother.|Billy Maximoff and [[Agatha Harkness]]|Familiar by Thy Side}}
Angry, Maximoff charged after [[Agatha Harkness]], demanding to know why she would kill [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]]. Harkness claimed she could not control it, but Maximoff refused to believe this, telling Harkness not to lie to him. Maximoff claimed she wanted Wu-Gulliver's power and that is what it had been about.
[[File:You're So Much Like Your Mother.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff is taunted by [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
[[Jennifer Kale]] agreed, saying that it was what all of it was about for any of them. All [[Lilia Calderu]] had to say was that death came for them all. A still angry Maximoff asked if that was really what it meant to be a witch, killing people for their own agenda; he defiantly declared that life was not for him. This got Harkness to chuckle a little bit as she leaned closer, asking if Maximoff was sure about that. Getting very serious, Harkness forced Maximoff to look at her as she told him he was so much like his [[Scarlet Witch|mother]].
[[File:Wiccan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff reveals himself]]
Maximoff looked at her sternly as she took her hands off his chin and walked away, still grinning. She then turned around, telling him to follow her as she called him her pet. In a fit of rage, Maximoff started controlling Calderu and Kale's minds to attack Harkness. He then had them throw Harkness into a vat of quick-sinking mud and watched as she became engulfed by the substance. Not stopping there, Maximoff threw Calderu and Kale into the mud as well and watched as they struggled and begged to be free. A blue crown then emerged on Maximoff's head.{{Ref|AAA105}}
[[File:Billy and the Sigil.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff breaking his sigil]]
Maximoff sat by a tree holding the wooden sigil. He then squeezed on it, destroying the sigil and letting it fall from his hand. Suddenly, he heard Harkness' voice from a distance, telling him that was quite the debut. She then mocked his old phrases, mimicking his faked confusion as to what a sigil was and his false craving for power. He corrected himself now, saying power was not what interested him. Harkness told him to continue telling himself that. Maximoff then asked when she figured out his identity.
[[File:Billy Kaplan on the Witches' Road.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff argues with [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
Harkness said she had a feeling when they first met, because even with a sigil in the way, he and Wanda had the same tell. Maximoff asked what it was and Harkness replied that it was very inconvenient for him. She also did not know for sure until he went mad just moments ago. Harkness soon said that it was nice to see him again, calling him "Billy". Maximoff then said "Billy" then "William" and realized she could hear his identity. Harkness' attention then moved on to Calderu and Kale, not knowing what to say about what Maximoff did. However, she brought up how many people she had killed, which she cannot remember the number of.
[[File:Wiccan's Lost Power.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff's powers fail to manifest]]
Growing angry again, Maximoff assured Harkness he was not like her, but Harkness sarcastically asked herself where she had heard that before. An intrigued Harkness then asked where he came across [[William Kaplan]]'s body, but Maximoff refused to give details. Harkness understood, telling Maximoff to not feel guilt about what he had done because he survived like witches had been doing for centuries. He survived, which is what makes him special and also makes him a witch.
[[File:Agatha Harkness and Billy Maximoff.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff is belittled by [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
Harkness then stated that they needed to make it to the end of the [[Witches' Road]], but Maximoff stopped her at "we", saying he did not need her and he did not know if he ever did. Maximoff then charged up his power, only for it not to emerge. This made Harkness start laughing as Maximoff said he could finish the road on his own. Harkness simply said he could not due to the power he could not control without throwing a tantrum. Maximoff yelled that he would figure it out.
[[File:I'm Not That Nice.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff decides to follow [[Agatha Harkness]]]]
Harkness then approached Maximoff, teasing him about what he could want at the end of the road since he already had power. She asked if it was to "find mama". However, she concluded that was not the case because she chose a [[Westview|town]] of strangers over her own children. She then realized there were two other Maximoffs; Billy had a twin, [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]]. Maximoff confessed that he knew Tommy was out there, but could not find him. Maximoff then told Harkness they would finish the road together, but he did not trust her. Harkness understood and walked forward, saying the last one to the next trial was a nice person. Maximoff remarked that he was not that nice.{{Ref|AAA106}}

