====[[Green Witch Trial|Resurrecting Tommy]]====
[[File:Billy Maximoff Body Bag.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff emerges from a body bag]]
{{Quote|He's got no one! Agatha, am I killing this boy so my [[Tommy Maximoff|brother]] can live?!|Billy Maximoff to [[Agatha Harkness]]|Follow Me My Friend / To Glory at the End}}
Maximoff found himself in a body bag and quickly unzipped it, revealing that he was in a [[Witches' Road Morgue|morgue]]. Soon, [[Agatha Harkness]] and [[Jennifer Kale]] popped out of the wall in drawers. Harkness was able to get out of her bag, but Kale struggled. Maximoff got out of his drawer to let Kale out, but Harkness told him not to, and Kale eventually freed herself. Kale noticed growing lights on the ceiling and suggested to Maximoff that they needed to grow something for the trial.
[[File:Green Witch Trial.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff and the [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] in the [[Green Witch Trial|final trial]]]]
Maximoff listened as Harkness asked Kale if there was any overlap between [[Magic#Earth Magic|Earth magic]] and [[Magic#Alchemy|Alchemy]], to which Kale replied that there was some. However, to Maximoff's disappointment, Kale was bound and could not use her magic. Kale began talking about her past and soon realized that Harkness was the one who bound her. Maximoff angrily asked Harkness if it was true, but Harkness simply said she didn't know it was Kale.
[[File:Jennifer Kale gets her magic back.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff sees [[Jennifer Kale]]'s [[Magic#Alchemy|magic]] return]]
Maximoff then watched as a determined Kale took a clump of Harkness' hair and bound her wrists with it before saying again and again that Harkness had no power over her; Maximoff realized that she was performing an unbinding ritual. Finally, Kale dropped to the ground, and when she rose again, her magic had returned. She then disappeared from the room. In a panic, Maximoff asked where she went, and Harkness responded that the [[Witches' Road]] had given her what she was missing.
[[File:Agatha helps Billy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff attempts to recall his memories]]
Harkness then told Maximoff to let her absorb his powers since she had come to the Road for power. Maximoff refused as he believed she would kill him in the process, so Harkness decided to help Maximoff get his [[Tommy Maximoff|brother]] a body. Sitting down, Harkness told Maximoff to focus on his last moments with Tommy. As Maximoff continued to be guided through the process, he heard [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] and [[Wanda Maximoff]]'s voices.
[[File:Agatha and Billy in Gowns.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Maximoff tries to find a body for his [[Tommy Maximoff|brother]]]]
Maximoff described his memory, saying he was about to fall asleep when the sound of his brother along with every other sound suddenly ceased. Maximoff was told by Harkness that it was simply Wanda dispelling the [[Hex]] and that even though he couldn't hear Tommy, he knew he was close. Harkness told Maximoff that he held Tommy within him but that he could not stay there. Sparks began to fall from the ceiling as Harkness grabbed Maximoff's head and told him to find a place for Tommy.

Maximoff began to see flashes of black and reported to Harkness, who asked him what Tommy would see when he looked down. Maximoff panted that he could not find a body, but Harkness encouraged him enough for Maximoff to see a [[Thomas Shepherd|boy]] underwater who had fallen victim to a prank in which he was drowned. As he saw the boy convulse and stop moving, Maximoff desperately asked Harkness if he was killing the boy so Tommy could live. However, the boy, now Tommy, then rose from the water, and Maximoff disappeared.{{Ref|AAA108}}

