====Realizing the Truth====
{{Quote|It was me.|Billy Maximoff|Follow Me My Friend / To Glory at the End}}
Reeling from his experiences, Maximoff pulled up his hood, made his way through the gathering Westview residents to where his car was still parked nearby and drove home. The frantic Kaplans greeted Maximoff, questioning his injuries and the fact that he had been gone for 24 hours.

After showering, Maximoff looked around at all of his magical memorabilia and began to realize that all of the elements of the Road were drawn from his own love for and fascination with magic. Maximoff recalled all of the comments that Harkness had made along the way, hinting at a connection between Maximoff and the Road, as well as [[Lilia Calderu]] telling him that Maximoff had enormous potential and the ability to turn all of his goals into reality. Maximoff finally realized the truth: he had inherited [[Scarlet Witch|his mother]]'s reality warping powers and had brought the Witches' Road to life from his own imagination.{{Ref|AAA108}}

====Reunion with Agatha Harkness====
{{Quote|One door closes."<br>"And another one opens."<br>"Let's go find [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]].|[[Agatha Harkness]] and Billy Maximoff|Maiden Mother Crone}}
{{Rewrite|summaries should not just be transcribing the dialogue that occurred on-screen}}
A disembodied voice chuckled at his realization and frightened Maximoff.{{Ref|AAA108}} It proved to be Harkness who had become a [[Ghosts|ghost]] in death and was seemingly enjoying her new state. Harkness claimed that she didn't sacrifice herself for Maximoff, but instead had taken a calculated risk, although Harkness was still figuring out the new rules of her existence. Maximoff asked if he had been the one to create the Road and Harkness told him that unlike Wanda, Maximoff had actually done something interesting with his power. The [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]] was just a con to lure other gullible witches and the Witches' Road wasn't real until Maximoff made it real. Maximoff was horrified as his creation of the Road meant that he was responsible for the deaths of the rest of the [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]], although Harkness pointed out that Maximoff had actually saved [[Jennifer Kale|Kale]]'s life while she had planned to kill everyone in her basement on day one. Harkness told Maximoff that he had to get used to this feeling if he wanted to be a witch, but he declared that that would never happen.

Maximoff returned to Harkness' house where he began performing a banishing spell for Harkness' ghost using her [[Agatha Harkness' Locket|locket]], telling Harkness that she didn't get a second chance, and it was time for Harkness to go to whatever afterlife awaited her. Despite Harkness' attempts to convince him to stop, Maximoff carried on with the spell, causing Harkness to flicker in and out of existence. Harkness finally admitted that she couldn't face her [[Nicholas Scratch|son]] and broke the spell by knocking her locket out of Maximoff's hands.

As Harkness retrieved her locket, Maximoff wiped away his tears and told Harkness that he was sure that Scratch would forgive her for whatever she did. Harkness revealed that when Maximoff said things like that, she reminded her of Scratch. Maximoff suggested that being a ghost might suit Harkness and the two could make a good team with Harkness serving as his spirit guide. While Harkness tended to kill her coven members, so did Maximoff. Turning to the door to the Witches' Road, Maximoff got rid of it for good, inscribing a memorial for [[Sharon Davis]], [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] and [[Lilia Calderu]] in its place. Maximoff and Harkness then left together to find [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]].{{Ref|AAA109}}

==Powers==
{{Quote|You are {{WPS|The Magician (tarot card)|The Magician}}. You have enormous potential and the ability to turn all of your goals into reality.|[[Lilia Calderu]] to Billy Maximoff|Death's Hand in Mine}}
*'''[[Magic]]''': Not only did Maximoff inherit magic from his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]], he has been studying witchcraft for about three years, thus he was knowledgeable and skilled enough to break a spell cast by his powerful mother.
**'''Psionics''': Like his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]], Maximoff has magical psionic abilities, which manifest as blue, glowing energy currents and mist-like shapes from his hands.
***'''Psychic Energy Manipulation''': [[File:Billy Maximoff (2023).png|thumb|250px|Maximoff halts a bullet with his telekinesis]] Maximoff has the ability to create and manipulate psionic energy.
****'''Telekinesis''': Maximoff was able to stop his [[Tommy Maximoff|brother]] from super speeding just by sticking his hand out. He also halted [[Tyler Hayward]]'s bullet with his telekinesis. He was able to telekinetically throw [[Lilia Calderu]] and [[Jennifer Kale]] off of the [[Witches' Road]] and pull his spell book into his hand from across the basement.
****'''Energy Projection''': After saving [[Agatha Harkness]] by blasting [[Death]], Wiccan was able to project energy into her, allowing her to absorb the energy and use it to heal.
***'''Mental Manipulation''': Maximoff is able to deploy a form of mind manipulation. He mentally paralyzed several [[S.W.O.R.D.]] agents during a [[Battle of Westview|confrontation]] in [[Westview]] while [[Tommy Maximoff]] ran by them. He was able to brainwash [[Lilia Calderu]] and [[Jennifer Kale]] into pushing [[Agatha Harkness]] off the [[Witches' Road]].
***'''Telepathy''': Maximoff was able to telepathically hear and feel [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] in distress while he was escaping from [[Westview]]. He was also able to read the minds of his [[Rebecca Kaplan|surrogate]] [[Jeff Kaplan|parents]] as well as the minds of [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] and [[Ralph Bohner]]. Wiccan also communicated with [[Agatha Harkness]] with his thoughts at the end of the [[Skirmish at Agnes O'Connor's House]].
***'''Clairvoyance''': Maximoff was able to see his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]] accidentally choking [[Westview]] civilians before it happened. He was also able to visualize mentally the events of another boy's death when he guided his twin brother's soul into his body.
***'''Fire Manipulation''': Maximoff lit a circle of candles with his mind.
**'''[[Magic#Chaos Magic|Chaos Magic]]''': Much like his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]], Maximoff can harness [[Magic#Chaos Magic|Chaos Magic]].<ref>[https://youtu.be/lvkxZKKPHE4?feature=shared&t=9836 'Agatha All Along' Finale Deep Dive, Plus Showrunner Jac Schaeffer | House of R]</ref><ref>[https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/agatha-all-along-nicholas-scratch-father-agatha-rio-backstory-post-credits-scene-1236197515/ ‘Agatha All Along’ Creator Explains Shocking Finale Twists, Agatha and Rio’s Backstory, Nicholas Scratch’s Father and Why There’s No Post-Credits Scene]</ref> He can shape and manipulate this magic for different effects, such as forming tangible constructs of energy or cast spells without incantation. His magic is primarily composed of blue energy, instead of his mother's red. Maximoff can wield Chaos Magic subconsciously without needing constant concentration to sustain the changes he has made. At first, Maximoff had no control over this power; however, with [[Agatha Harkness]]' help, Maximoff gained more experience in the control of his magic.
***'''Reality Warping''': Like his [[Wanda Maximoff|mother]], Maximoff is a being capable of spontaneous creation. He can warp reality at his will and wield his magic subconsciously without needing constant concentration to sustain the changes he has made. His reality warping abilities began initially on a small scale; however, as time progressed, his powers have grown exponentially.
****'''Transformation''': ''To be added''
****'''Pocket Dimension Creation''': With his reality-warping abilities, Maximoff was able to make the legend of the [[Witches' Road]] real, as well as subconsciously manipulate the elements, trials, and rules of the Road.
**'''[[Magic#Witchcraft|Witchcraft]]''': As a witch, Maximoff has astute knowledge on the supernatural and the mystic arts.
***'''Spell Casting''': Maximoff has the power to cause change to his surroundings by reciting incantations. He performed a ritual to create a broomstick, giving it the ability to fly.
****'''Spell Negation''': Maximoff was able to cast a spell that negated the effects of [[Wanda Maximoff]]'s mind and reality warping abilities to break [[Agatha Harkness]] free from Wanda's spell.
****'''Banishment''': Maximoff attempted to banish [[Agatha Harkness]]' ghost using a [[Agatha Harkness' Locket|personal item]] of hers, however he failed due to Harkness knocking the locket out his hand.
**'''Resurrection''': Maximoff is capable of transferring his soul into a recently [[William Kaplan|deceased body]] and reviving it without the being's pre-existent soul. [[Death]], a [[Cosmic Entities|cosmic entity]] of nigh-limitless power, could not claim his soul as Maximoff would just continue to return after each death. His first resurrection was done instinctively as Maximoff had no idea how he did it. With [[Agatha Harkness]]' help, Maximoff successfully resurrected the disembodied [[Tommy Maximoff]] by guiding his soul into a recently deceased body in a similar manner.
**'''Levitation''': Wiccan levitated in the air above [[Agnes O'Connor's House]] before lowering himself to the ground.
*'''Age Manipulation''': Maximoff and his twin brother [[Tommy Maximoff|Tommy]] have both been shown to have the ability to change their ages at will, each time aging up around five years.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Vision Residence]]''': Billy Maximoff was born in [[Wanda Maximoff]] and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]]'s house, where he and his [[Tommy Maximoff|brother]] grew up. Maximoff and Vision raised the twins, who aged themselves up so that they could keep [[Sparky]] in the house. They hosted who they believed to be [[Ralph Bohner|Pietro Maximoff]] in their house, though Billy got nervous around him. The Maximoffs returned to the Vision residence as the [[Hex]] was dissolved, and Billy and Tommy were sent to bed for the last time.
*'''[[Kaplan Residence]]''': Maximoff took over the body of [[William Kaplan]], but developed amnesia and therefore did not know who he was. Believing himself to truly be Kaplan, Maximoff lived in his house and bedroom with [[Rebecca Kaplan|Rebecca]] and [[Jeff Kaplan]]. Maximoff decorated his room with his interests and investigated the connection between the [[Kaplan Family Car Crash]] and the [[Westview Anomaly]] from the room. He showed [[Eddie (Boyfriend)|Eddie]] the findings and researched [[Agatha Harkness]] from his bedroom. Maximoff returned home from the [[Witches' Road]], met by concern from his parents. Maximoff looked around his room and saw elements of it which reminded him of the Road, leading him to realize that he was the one who created it. Harkness then appeared in Maximoff's room as a ghost, leaving Maximoff to leave the house again to try to banish Harkness.
*'''[[Agnes O'Connor's House]]''': Maximoff and his [[Tommy Maximoff|brother]] were [[Kidnapping of Billy and Tommy Maximoff|brought]] to [[Agnes O'Connor]]'s house under the guise of being for the purpose of allowing [[Wanda Maximoff]] alone time. However, after briefly genuinely taking care of them, "O'Connor" took the two of them hostage and held them prisoner in the basement of the house. O'Connor, whose real name was [[Agatha Harkness]], later took the twins hostage outside of the house. Three years later, Maximoff had amnesia due to the transfer of his soul to [[William Kaplan]]'s body and returned to the house, finding Harkness under a spell, believing herself to be O'Connor and a detective. Maximoff cast a spell to [[Liberation of Agatha Harkness|free]] Harkness, but it did not take affect right away and "O'Connor" "[[Kidnapping of Billy Maximoff|arrested]]" Maximoff, shoving him in her closet until the following morning. Maximoff and Harkness [[Search for Coven Members|organized]] a [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] together, and Maximoff [[Attack on Agnes O'Connor's House|defended]] the house, summoning a door to the [[Witches' Road]] for them to escape. They returned from the Road and [[Skirmish at Agnes O'Connor's House|fought]] [[Death]] together in Harkness' backyard, and Maximoff then left as the house was crowded. Maximoff returned in an attempt to banish Harkness' ghost, but ultimately reconciled with Harkness and left to find [[Tommy Maximoff]].
*'''[[Hokey Pokey Bowl]]''': As [[William Kaplan]], Maximoff worked at the Hokey Pokey Bowl over a summer, hoping to make enough money to buy a record by [[Lorna Wu and the Coral Shore]]. However, he did not earn enough.

