==Trivia==
*In the comics, Billy Maximoff is the son of [[Wanda Maximoff]], created using a piece of [[Mephisto]]'s soul. Billy Maximoff eventually ceased to exist, although his soul was reincarnated years later in '''[[William Kaplan|William "Billy" Kaplan]]'''. As a result of having Billy Maximoff's soul, Kaplan had access to his magical, reality-warping powers that he had inherited from Wanda. Kaplan then became a member of the [[w:c:marvel:Young Avengers|Young Avengers]] under the name of '''Asgardian''' before changing his name to Wiccan.
*Maximoff was named by his father [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]], who named him after {{WPS|William Shakespeare}}.
**In the comics, he was named after [[Simon Williams]].
**In the comics, Vision's self-constructed son [[w:c:marvel:Vin|Vin]] has an obsession with Shakespeare.
*In ''[[WandaVision]]'', Maximoff usually wears red while his brother [[Tommy Maximoff]] wears green, a reference to the costumes of their reincarnations in the comics.
*Maximoff's outfit on the [[Witches' Road]] has runes that Maximoff stitched himself. Upon conjuring the Wiccan outfit, the runes were transferred over, and served as magical protection. Additionally, the patterns on the suit mimics [[Scarlet Witch]]'s sleeves while the cape is based on [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]]'s, serving as a way for Wiccan to have both of his parents with him.{{Ref|TMoAAA}}

==Behind the Scenes==
*In the comics, Billy Maximoff reincarnated into Billy Kaplan and then became Wiccan. However, [[Jac Schaeffer]], the showrunner of ''[[Agatha All Along]]'', found the comics history too confusing and decided to simplify the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] version of events by having [[William Kaplan]] die, allowing for Billy Maximoff's soul to migrate into Kaplan's dead body, live life as Kaplan, and eventually become Wiccan.<ref>[https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/agatha-all-along-billy-maximoff-return-evan-peters-cameo-1236181984/ <nowiki>Billy Maximoff Returns: Joe Locke and ‘Agatha All Along’ Creator on Hiding His Identity, ‘Wacky’ Fan Theories and Bringing Back [SPOILER] From ‘WandaVision’</nowiki>]</ref><ref name="JacSchafferInterview">[https://www.thewrap.com/agatha-all-along-episode-6-billy-evan-peters-jac-schaffer-interview/ ‘Agatha All Along’ Showrunner Talks Episode 6: Billy’s Backstory, Agatha’s Secret and That Cameo]</ref>
*[[Jack Fisher]] auditioned for the role of Billy Maximoff in ''[[WandaVision]]''.<ref>[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=dNSghQ1egZg Jack Fisher - Audition Tape for WandaVision]</ref>
*[[Jackson Robert Scott]] was a reference for Billy Maximoff in ''[[On a Very Special Episode...]]'' and ''[[All-New Halloween Spooktacular!]]''.
*[[Brittania Fader]] was a stunt double for [[Julian Hilliard]] in the role of Billy Maximoff.
*[[Rowbie Orsatti]] and [[Jesse LaFlair]] were stunt doubles for [[Joe Locke]] in the role of Billy Maximoff.

